news.title: L&T may exit Hyderabad metro as free bus rides hurt business
news.para: The Telangana government's free bus ride scheme for women has led to a decrease in Hyderabad Metro's ridership, prompting L&T to contemplate exiting the project. L&T faces financial concerns as the metro project is now classified as a non-core asset.

news.title: South Korea tightens scrutiny to speed up real estate restructuring
news.para: House prices in South Korea have been falling since June, 2023, as high interest rates weighed on demand, and worries about debt repayments at construction firms have grown after a mid-sized builder's decision in December to reschedule its debt.

news.title: NCLAT halts ATS project's insolvency process
news.para: NCLAT paused CIRP for ATS Group's Knightsbridge project in Sector 124, allowing time for responses and construction supervision under Sunil Gaur. Rera funds utilized, pending final disposal of appeals.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji Group seeks time to clear payments from bondholders
news.para: The company is required to pay around 14 billion rupees ($167.62 million) to bondholders of Goswami Infratech when it services the debt of another group company Sterling Investment Corp.

news.title: Supreme Court admits petition on imposition of GST on joint development pacts
news.para: The Supreme Court admits a petition challenging GST imposition on transfer of development rights in joint development agreements, impacting real estate projects nationwide.

news.title: ASK Property Fund exits from Naiknavare Developers' Pune project with 21% IRR
news.para: ASK Property Fund had invested Rs 80 crore in this project in 2018. The recent exit has achieved a targeted IRR of 21% and a 2x multiple of the capital invested.

news.title: Nimbus Realty launches 11.9 acres project at Yamuna Expressway - Nimbus The Palm Village
news.para: Comprising 3 BHK independent floors, 1 BHK furnished apartments, and High Retail street shops, Nimbus The Palm Village caters to discerning individuals seeking a premium lifestyle.

news.title: Panaji: Smart City work along Caculo Mall stretch may miss May 31 deadline
news.para: IPSCDL said that the cumulative target for completing all road works and making the road functional is May 31, however, this particular stretch may take a “little longer”.

news.title: NGT forms panel to inspect 'illegal' brick kilns in Mathura
news.para: A bench of NGT Chairperson Justice Prakash Shrivastava and expert member A Senthil Vel noted the submissions of the petitioner's counsel, as per which, around 360 brick kilns were operating in the district and several of them were violating the norms.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government has inaugurated 28,824 apartments in last three years
news.para: Soon after this government assumed office (in May 7, 2021) Tamil Nadu Urban Habitat Development Board has inaugurated 28,824 residential apartments built at a cost of Rs 3,197.94 crore", the release said.

news.title: Fashion companies' dull show worries Nexus Select Trust
news.para: The concerns are weighing on Nexus as India's first publicly listed retail Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT) is looking to invest Rs 1,000 crore in acquiring three malls in Hyderabad to grow the total portfolio to 20 malls and 11 million sq ft.

news.title: IL&FS seeks fresh MMRDA approval for transfer of headquarter in Mumbai
news.para: IL&FS applies for MMRDA approval to transfer its BKC headquarters to Brookfield Asset Management. NCLT's transfer is pending, causing delays. Brookfield progresses towards property acquisition as IL&FS aims to manage debt through asset monetization efforts.

news.title: Anarock reports increase in net revenue by 36% in FY24
news.para: Homegrown Anarock was established by Anuj Puri in April 2017 after serving as country head for 10 years in an international property consultancy firm.

news.title: Bombay high court grants bail to landowner in building collapse case
news.para: On May 1, the Narpoli Police Station in Thane arrested Patil for offenses punishable under sections 304(2), 337, 338, and 427 read with 34 of the Indian Penal Code.

news.title: Leverage technology to keep tabs on construction in Aravallis: Rajasthan HC
news.para: The Jodhpur bench of Rajasthan High Court has directed the govt to explain that how this technology can be leveraged to tag and demarcate the hills in the lake district.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government cancels allotment of two land parcels in Noida to M3M Group
news.para: The move comes as a big blow for M3M, which is already facing Enforcement Directorate investigations. It also puts home buyers in a quandary as both the projects were launched and parts of them sold.

news.title: London's Canary Wharf eyes overhaul of HSBC's skyscraper: Sources
news.para: Landlord Canary Wharf Group (CWG) invited around 20 architectural practices to submit proposals for the 45-floor building and began shortlisting designs in recent weeks, three sources familiar with the matter said.

news.title: China's Country Garden repays onshore coupons within grace period
news.para: Country Garden, which defaulted on $11 billion of offshore bonds and extended other onshore bond repayments late last year, said on Thursday it aimed to make the payment and additional interest incurred by Monday.

news.title: Delhi court refuses to extend Supertech chairman's interim bail
news.para: The Additional Sessions Judge Devender Kumar Jangala in an order passed on Friday dismissed his plea and directed jail authorities to provide necessary prescribed medical treatment to him and allow him to carry the medicines, as prescribed by the doctors treating him.

news.title: Delhi HC issues notice to CBI on plea of Dheeraj Wadhawan seeking bail on medical grounds
news.para: Dheeraj Wadhawan has approached the High Court against the trial court order refusing him bail on medical grounds. He is under treatment at his home in Mumbai after discharge from the hospital post-spinal surgery.
